    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="651"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6381</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-13T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cipher telegrams of August 9, 8 p.m., and August 11, 11 p.m. The Department
                    believes that the character of China’s participation <pb facs="0628" n="456"
                        xml:id="pg_456"/> in the war should be decided by her after consultation
                    with all the Allied Governments. Consult your Allied colleagues informally and
                    report their views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
